President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Michael Peter Huerta was nominated for Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration. Huerta is currently the Deputy Administrator of the FAA and has been serving as Acting Administrator since December 2011. Robert James Grey, Jr. was nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. He is currently a partner at Hunton & Williams LLP and a mediator with the McCammon Mediation Group. John G. Levi was nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. He is a partner at Sidley Austin LLP and was first appointed to the Board by President Obama in March 2010. Laurie Mikva was nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. She is a Commissioner on the Illinois Court of Claims and teaches at Northwestern University Law School. Martha Minow was nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. She is the Dean of Harvard Law School and previously served as the William Henry Bloomberg Professor of Law. Gloria Valencia-Weber was nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. She is a professor at the University of New Mexico School of Law and specializes in Native American/American Indian Law.